(1) The proper officer shall, in respect of each beer hall for which he is proper officer — (a) keep a book in which shall clearly be recorded in the English language an account of the quantity of traditional beer sold, used or otherwise disposed of in each month , the quantity of traditional beer on hand at the end of each month and the amount of the levy paid in respect of each month ; (b) transmit to the Controller with the amount of each levy paid by the proprietor , a correct and legible return, in duplicate, in the form approved by the Controller , of the quantity of traditional beer sold, used or otherwise disposed of in the month in respect of which the levy is paid, and the quantity of traditional beer on hand, at the end of that month ; (c) furnish the Controller or an officer with such information as he may require in relation to the operations of the beer hall .
